Thomas Howard (f 9; 1537/8–1572) was ninth duke of Norfolk and fifteenth earl of Surrey
      from 25 August 1554, with residences at Charterhouse, Middlesex and Kenninghall, Norfolk;
      executed for treason. See P&P.

Edward Somerset (f [8v]; c 1550–1627/8) was ninth earl of Worcester
       from 21 February 1588/9, with seat at Raglan Castle, Monmouthshire and residence at Hackney,
       Middlesex. See P&P.

Edward Somerset (f [6]; c 1550–1627/8) was ninth earl of Worcester
      from 21 February 1588/9, with seat at Raglan, Monmouthshire and residence at Hackney,
      Middlesex. See P&P.

Sir Thomas Erpingham (1357-1428) was lord chamberlain of the Royal Household to Henry IV
      from 1399, and was one of Henry V's most important commanders at the Battle of Agincourt,
      with residence at Erpingham, Norfolk.
